2026-03-27T09:59:15.950Z JOY-005D item.created "Auto-add and auto-commit for Joy-managed files" [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-27T09:59:44.688Z JOY-005D comment.added "Config keys in workflow section:\n- auto-add: true|false (default true) -- git add after writing versioned files\n- auto-commit: true|false (default false) -- git commit after each Joy operation\n- auto-push: true|false (default false) -- git push after auto-commit\n\nApplies to all versioned Joy files: items, logs, milestones, releases, project.yaml, config.defaults.yaml, .gitignore. Does NOT apply to gitignored files (config.yaml, credentials.yaml, .joy/ai/, tool configs).\n\nImplementation: joy-core write helpers (write_yaml, ensure_gitignore, etc.) check config and call git add. Auto-commit wraps the CLI command execution -- one commit per joy command, not per file. Message format: 'joy: <command summary> <item-id>'.\n\nProgression: auto-add is safe and low-friction (default on). Auto-commit is opt-in for solo developers who want zero-ceremony. Auto-push is opt-in for teams who want instant sync." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
2026-03-27T10:01:53.053Z JOY-005D comment.added "Revised: single config key instead of three booleans.\n\nworkflow:\n  auto-git: add    # off | add | commit | push\n\nEach level implies the previous: push = add + commit + push. Default: add (safe, low-friction). Off for users who want full manual control." [horst.schwarz@joydev.com]
